main event: An unidentified object was observed over Finland for 10 minutes on February 12, 1961.
interesting points: The object was described as having a size or shape of a round plate with edges that were not sharply defined.
The object exhibited some fluctuation of light and disappeared from sight in the middle of its path of travel.
The report includes observations from four Finnish planes in various parts of Finland, all of which were flying above cloud formations.
The object appeared suddenly and could not have gone into the vision field behind the clouds, indicating it was not a natural phenomenon.
The object moved towards the north at an altitude of 20-30 degrees above the horizon, and was observed by multiple pilots in different directions, suggesting it was not a stable object or movement.
sighted object: a round plate-shaped object with fluctuating light
